WHO   — COMMODORE 64 · C64 — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — The best-selling computer of all time was also one of the great game machines: a 6510 CPU, the VIC-II graphics chip with hardware sprites and smooth scrolling, and the legendary SID sound chip whose three-voice synthesis still inspires musicians. Sixty-four kilobytes, and a culture.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
